discourse_list.title: Transfer DAI.e from metamask to coinbase

content.content: Yesterday I tried to transfer some ERC-20 DAI.e tokens from my metamask wallet (avalanche network) to my Coinbase exchange (sending them to the DAI address and associated with my account).  On snowtrace, the transaction was successful, so much so that in the address where I transferred them they appear, the problem is that nothing has arrived on coinbase!  How can I access those tokens now?  I ask you to help me because it was not small change let’s say … thanks in advance

I know it can take a little while to show up on Coinbase but a day seems long. A have had a couple times where I needed to close and re-open my browser for it to work but this is beyond my purview. I hope it shows up eventually for you.
Are you sure you sent them to the same network? I mean, from Avalanche to Avalanche, if you sent to an exchange address that does not support that network, you lost the funds.
This topic was automatically closed after 90 days. New replies are no longer allowed.
